HEADWORD: Tineman
<hw>Tine"man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Tinemen</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[Probably akin to
<ets>tine</ets> to shut or inclose.]</ety> <fld>(O. Eng. Forest
Law)</fld> <def>An officer of the forest who had the care of vert and
venison by night.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

